Per discussion on the maintainers list / meetings, we are now ready to remove `#align`, and it's time to do it!

This PR is generated by running:

```
find . -name "*.lean" -not -path "./lake/*" -exec sed -i '/^set_option linter.uppercaseLean3 false/d' {} +
find . -name "*.lean" -not -path "./lake/*" -exec sed -i '/^set_option align.precheck false/d' {} +
find . -name "*.lean" -not -path "./lake/*" -exec sed -i -e '/^$/N;/^\n#align/d' -e '/^#align/d' {} +
find . -name "*.lean" -not -path "./lake/*" -exec sed -i -e '/^$/N;/^\n#noalign/d' -e '/^#noalign/d' {} +
rm Mathlib/Init/Align.lean
find . -name "*.lean" -not -path "./lake/*" -exec sed -i '/^import Mathlib.Init.Align/d' {} +
find . -name "*.lean" -not -path "./lake/*" -exec sed -i -e '1{/^$/d;}' {} +
find . -name "*.lean" -not -path "./lake/*" -exec sed -i '/^import Mathlib.Mathport.Rename/d' {} +
```
